inlineContent.text: type defines attributes that apply to an entire attributed string, and not to specific ranges of characters. You specify these attributes when writing an attributed string to disk, or reading text from a file on disk. Use these attributes to specify metadata about the overall document, including its author or title, page margin details, font-scaling options for cross-platform interchange, and more.
